WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.040
JEREMIAH: <i>Thomas Michael Shelby...</i>

00:02.720 --> 00:04.360
TOMMY: <i>Today is my wedding day.</i>

00:04.920 --> 00:05.920
Take the photograph!

00:06.800 --> 00:09.360
TOMMY: <i>The Russians have made contact.</i>
ARTHUR: <i>On your wedding night.</i>

00:09.440 --> 00:12.000
Whoever it is up there,
he gave the wrong name.

00:12.080 --> 00:13.760
Can you do it?
Can you kill?

00:13.960 --> 00:15.440
You know
why he didn't come, don't you?

00:15.560 --> 00:16.560
My bloody man.

00:16.800 --> 00:18.440
There was a fire at his restaurant.

00:18.560 --> 00:20.840
No fraternizing with the foreigners.

00:20.960 --> 00:22.760
There's a cavalry officer.

00:23.200 --> 00:24.960
In March, we'll be engaged.

00:25.120 --> 00:26.920
JOHN: <i>But you want to try things first.</i>

00:27.680 --> 00:29.480
RUBEN: <i>I'm Ruben Oliver,
portrait artist.</i>

00:30.040 --> 00:31.040
You have my card.

00:31.200 --> 00:33.600
What was in your heart was beautiful.

00:34.600 --> 00:35.600
-(GUNSHOT)
-(PANTING)

00:36.000 --> 00:39.520
Just get this business done
and get away from things like this.

00:39.600 --> 00:40.600
Promise me.

00:41.040 --> 00:42.080
I promise.

00:42.720 --> 00:44.080
I will make us safe.

00:45.360 --> 00:47.360
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

01:55.040 --> 01:56.880
NUTLEY: Your brothers came to my house.

01:58.240 --> 02:01.120
They said the Peaky Blinders
had business with me.

02:03.200 --> 02:05.480
TOMMY: You're not afraid of me.

02:13.680 --> 02:14.680
So,

02:15.480 --> 02:17.880
what is it you want
from a simple working man?

02:18.720 --> 02:19.800
Fear.

02:24.920 --> 02:27.080
Poor Mr Nutley drank too much.

02:28.640 --> 02:32.320
He went for a piss on the train tracks
that run behind the factory.

02:33.040 --> 02:34.280
Train came.

02:36.400 --> 02:38.680
They found his body in Saltley
broken into bits.

02:38.800 --> 02:40.360
I know what you do.

02:41.400 --> 02:42.800
Tell me what you want.

02:48.600 --> 02:49.600
There.

02:50.480 --> 02:54.360
The lot's complete warehouse.
Bays 4, 5 and 6.

02:54.560 --> 02:55.840
You have the keys?

02:56.120 --> 02:57.840
Yes, I have keys.

02:59.040 --> 03:00.480
What's in Bay 4?

03:01.560 --> 03:04.960
Completed type 40s and type 21 s
waiting for the paint shop.

03:05.800 --> 03:07.040
Bay 5?

03:07.480 --> 03:09.640
-NUTLEY: Paint shop and parts.
-Uh-huh.

03:10.920 --> 03:12.160
So, it's Bay 6.

03:12.680 --> 03:13.840
What is?

03:14.800 --> 03:15.960
(INHALES SHARPLY)

03:16.040 --> 03:17.920
Give me the keys to Bay 6.

03:19.600 --> 03:21.240
It's just old stock in storage.

03:22.200 --> 03:24.440
Give me the keys to Bay 6.

03:26.400 --> 03:27.960
(SIGHS)

03:38.400 --> 03:39.920
(KEYS JANGLING)

03:51.560 --> 03:52.760
For your trouble.

03:53.880 --> 03:55.320
Give it to your charity.

04:04.440 --> 04:07.040
I'm only doing this
for the safety of my family.

04:51.360 --> 04:52.400
(GRUNTS)

05:11.080 --> 05:12.400
(SIGHS)

05:12.480 --> 05:13.560
(SNIFFS)

05:31.520 --> 05:32.600
(SIGHS)

05:33.120 --> 05:37.480
HUGHES: So, will it be just boys in your
charitable institution or girls as well?

05:39.560 --> 05:40.880
Both.

05:42.040 --> 05:43.320
You must divide them.

05:44.320 --> 05:46.440
You know how the little creatures
can get.

05:48.520 --> 05:51.360
Where are your people?
You said they'd be here by 5:00.

05:52.200 --> 05:53.800
HUGHES: They are a law unto themselves.

05:54.440 --> 05:56.800
You can never quite grasp who they are.

05:57.640 --> 05:59.200
Like gripping wet soap.

06:01.440 --> 06:03.160
I've done my research.

06:04.480 --> 06:06.040
Erm...

06:06.200 --> 06:10.160
Perhaps you know them
as the, uh, Economic League.

06:11.040 --> 06:14.400
Only once did I get a letter from them
headed "The Vigilance Committee."

06:14.600 --> 06:16.320
Which tips the hand a little.

06:16.600 --> 06:18.400
(CLICKS TONGUE) No.

06:18.760 --> 06:21.560
The name I've heard is Section D.

06:21.840 --> 06:24.560
-(POURING DRINK)
-That's what Special Branch calls them.

06:25.320 --> 06:29.080
Business men, MPs, army officers.

06:30.880 --> 06:32.160
(EXHALES)

06:33.160 --> 06:36.440
HUGHES: Yes, it will be fun to bring
such men to a Gypsy scrapyard.

06:36.520 --> 06:37.760
(SCOFFS)

06:39.480 --> 06:41.040
You asked for privacy.

06:41.480 --> 06:45.680
Since the election, the government
has decided that we are the enemy.

06:46.920 --> 06:50.280
When all we're trying to do
is save the country from revolution.

06:52.480 --> 06:54.880
Are you political, Mr Shelby?

06:56.280 --> 06:57.600
Because these Odd Fellows believe

06:57.680 --> 07:01.200
that the time is coming soon
when everyone must choose a side.

07:03.360 --> 07:05.640
Are your people coming
or are they not coming?

07:06.280 --> 07:09.480
Mr Shelby, you will learn that
these men are far too grand

07:09.560 --> 07:11.280
for the clock to govern them.

07:12.840 --> 07:15.920
You'll get used to meeting
in the small hours of the morning.

07:16.680 --> 07:17.800
They're like monks.

07:21.400 --> 07:24.120
So, when is your
charitable institute opening?

07:24.480 --> 07:26.400
(EXHALES) When I fucking say.

07:28.360 --> 07:31.240
Well, I'll stop by from time to time

07:31.320 --> 07:33.640
to hear confession
from the little creatures.

07:35.480 --> 07:38.160
You'll meet Mr Patrick Jarvis, MP.

07:38.240 --> 07:40.280
He'll probably want to become a trustee.

07:41.240 --> 07:44.960
It's just his thing, to drop by
in the evenings after a few drinks.

07:45.880 --> 07:50.440
We'll make it a formal arrangement
as part of the bigger deal between us.

07:52.360 --> 07:54.800
-I will have an office there.
-(CLEARING THROAT)

07:57.360 --> 07:58.880
(TOMMY SNIFFS)

08:00.000 --> 08:01.160
(SPITS)

08:02.000 --> 08:03.040
Ah!

08:04.280 --> 08:07.000
My God. Some devil gets into you,
doesn't it, boy?

08:09.680 --> 08:11.320
Mr Shelby,

08:11.880 --> 08:16.880
if I want to play the squire in your
place of false charity, then I will.

08:17.920 --> 08:21.120
Ambition for respectability
doesn't make you a saint.

08:21.720 --> 08:22.920
Am I wrong?

08:24.720 --> 08:26.440
(BELL TOLLING)

08:27.880 --> 08:29.720
Oh, Lord. That's 6:00, is it?

08:31.760 --> 08:34.400
Well, I wish you a good day.

08:35.200 --> 08:36.680
Where the fuck are you going?

08:36.760 --> 08:38.320
Did I not make it clear?

08:39.120 --> 08:41.440
They said if they weren't here
by morning prayers

08:41.520 --> 08:43.320
then the meeting has been cancel led.

08:44.640 --> 08:48.360
Perhaps Mr Jarvis has been held up
at the House of Commons.

08:49.280 --> 08:52.320
Perhaps Admiral Hall's been held up
at the House of Lords.

08:53.440 --> 08:54.800
Am I impressing you?

08:55.960 --> 08:58.720
Or perhaps they have decided
they don't care for doing business

08:58.800 --> 09:00.960
with Gypsies in scrap metal yards

09:01.360 --> 09:03.600
which would be a poor outcome for you.

09:03.680 --> 09:06.200
You give them a message
from me, Priest.

09:08.280 --> 09:10.760
You tell them I've been to the factories

09:11.160 --> 09:13.680
and the armoured vehicles
are in good condition.

09:16.280 --> 09:17.680
HUGHES: How many?

09:19.640 --> 09:21.080
Twenty-seven.

09:21.960 --> 09:23.800
And the foreman is ours.

09:26.240 --> 09:28.040
This is someone you'll meet.

09:28.680 --> 09:30.480
Today, at the Ritz.

09:31.160 --> 09:32.520
I have meetings today.

09:33.040 --> 09:35.680
You have one meeting, this one.

09:36.480 --> 09:37.720
In London.

09:39.120 --> 09:41.000
So, you'd best catch the milk train.

09:48.640 --> 09:50.280
(VIOLIN PLAYING)

09:52.520 --> 09:54.400
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

10:22.280 --> 10:23.960
(VIOLIN STOPS PLAYING)

10:40.120 --> 10:41.120
Cold.

10:41.600 --> 10:42.600
My apologies, sir.

10:42.840 --> 10:44.640
And how many times
I asked you to tell them

10:44.720 --> 10:46.520
about sending us the servant's crockery.

10:46.600 --> 10:48.960
BUTLER: I have no control
over the choice of service, sir.

10:49.040 --> 10:52.600
Hmm, and what about yesterday's eggs
and last year's fish

10:53.000 --> 10:55.280
and last century's tea leaves
in a cracked pot.

10:55.400 --> 10:58.960
Sir, I have a list of today's social
engagements, if you'd like to hear them.

10:59.040 --> 11:00.320
Oh, are we in a rush today?

11:00.440 --> 11:02.200
-I have duties at the main house, sir.
-Mmm.

11:03.480 --> 11:05.480
BUTLER: Luncheon at The Ritz
with Duke Michail Michailovich.

11:06.680 --> 11:07.800
(LEON SPEAKS IN RUSSIAN)

11:07.960 --> 11:09.280
Cancel led.

11:09.760 --> 11:13.400
-(IN ENGLISH) What reason?
-BUTLER: He says he is unwell, sir.

11:15.400 --> 11:17.880
You are due to have tea at 3:00

11:17.960 --> 11:21.840
with Prince Sevlod lanovich
and Lady Mary Lewington, sir.

11:23.160 --> 11:25.440
Mmm! Good.

11:25.560 --> 11:28.120
I miss out on the bore
and meet the beauty.

11:28.280 --> 11:30.120
However, in the absence of the Duke,

11:30.280 --> 11:34.120
the, er, Prince and the Lady
too have cancel led, sir.

11:37.640 --> 11:40.280
Other than that,
your day is, er, your own.

11:41.760 --> 11:43.560
You do have one business appointment

11:44.120 --> 11:48.720
to discuss automobiles
with a Mr Thomas Shelby, sir.

11:53.640 --> 11:54.920
(HORSE WHINNYING)

12:15.240 --> 12:17.920
You asked for a meeting out in the open.

12:18.720 --> 12:21.760
Fresh air and the fine aroma of shit.

12:23.240 --> 12:24.520
"Neutral ground", you said.

12:25.480 --> 12:27.920
VICENTE: This is hardly neutral ground.

12:28.240 --> 12:31.120
Well, it's what you've got.

12:31.400 --> 12:33.880
So, <i>por favor,</i>

12:35.160 --> 12:36.160
sit down.

12:36.800 --> 12:38.600
-VICENTE: Where is Thomas?
-He got called away.

12:38.720 --> 12:39.720
He'd said he'd be here.

12:39.840 --> 12:40.840
ARTHUR: Yeah, he is busy.

12:41.000 --> 12:43.400
And I just told you he got called away.
What do you want?

12:49.760 --> 12:51.840
There has been a peace

12:52.680 --> 12:54.160
between the Peaky Blinders

12:54.240 --> 12:56.960
and the Changretta family
for two years now...

12:57.120 --> 12:58.200
Do you want some tea or not?

12:59.880 --> 13:02.720
Here, Finn, pour the Italians
some English tea. Go on.

13:03.880 --> 13:05.760
We don't want fucking tea.

13:10.600 --> 13:12.360
We want an explanation.

13:12.680 --> 13:13.920
Well, I'll have fucking tea.

13:14.320 --> 13:16.040
Explanation for what?

13:16.760 --> 13:20.800
The Little Venice Restaurant
on Forge Street was burnt down.

13:21.200 --> 13:23.440
No. No. Couldn't have been us,
we was at a wedding.

13:23.600 --> 13:28.600
You burnt it down to stop my son
being at that same wedding.

13:28.880 --> 13:30.040
He wasn't missed.

13:30.280 --> 13:31.400
(LAUGHS)

13:32.720 --> 13:33.960
(CHUCKLES)

13:34.800 --> 13:36.600
You are such big boys now.

13:37.480 --> 13:41.280
But once you borrowed clothes from us
to look like men.

13:41.800 --> 13:43.840
-How's the tea, Arthur? Is it...
-(SPLASHES)

13:45.960 --> 13:47.320
It's cold.

13:50.040 --> 13:51.760
Please tell Tommy

13:52.440 --> 13:54.920
that we pay him
whatever he asks us to pay.

13:55.000 --> 13:57.800
We stay out of the city
and off the tracks.

13:58.520 --> 14:01.800
But you tell him from me

14:02.880 --> 14:07.400
that my son will walk
with any woman in this city.

14:07.680 --> 14:09.240
Any woman he chooses.

14:09.720 --> 14:13.480
Even if that woman works
for the emperor, Thomas Shelby.

14:13.960 --> 14:15.600
My son is in love...

14:15.960 --> 14:17.200
(JOHN SNORTS)

14:17.720 --> 14:20.280
JOHN: (CHUCKLING) Sorry. Do excuse me.

14:20.960 --> 14:23.240
(SNIFFS) Carry on.

14:26.880 --> 14:31.360
VICENTE: And if he wishes,
he will walk with the woman he loves.

14:31.840 --> 14:32.840
OK.

14:34.600 --> 14:35.800
You know...

14:36.400 --> 14:38.720
It would be hard for your son
to walk anywhere

14:39.480 --> 14:41.880
with a bullet in each knee, wouldn't it?

14:50.040 --> 14:51.120
Too much.

14:53.360 --> 14:55.560
You said too much, my friend.

14:56.520 --> 14:59.200
Sabini says, "Suck and swallow." But no.

15:00.320 --> 15:01.320
Too much.

15:02.600 --> 15:04.560
I spit. (SPITS)

15:05.120 --> 15:07.240
(VICENTE SPEAKING ITALIAN)

15:10.480 --> 15:13.200
JOHN: Oh. OK. A bit strong.

15:18.680 --> 15:21.160
-(LAUGHS) Fucking hell.
-Isiah.

15:22.280 --> 15:24.960
Put two extra men on our pubs
in Nechells.

15:25.640 --> 15:27.080
What are you talking about, Arthur?

15:27.320 --> 15:29.120
We're not scared of
fucking Eyeties any more.

15:29.280 --> 15:32.520
Don't tell Tommy about the chair
and clean this fucking shit up.

15:34.240 --> 15:36.480
We're not scared of fucking wops!

15:36.640 --> 15:38.000
(GRUMBLES) All right, John.

15:39.000 --> 15:40.320
Arthur!

15:45.680 --> 15:46.880
TOMMY: Hello, Ada.

15:49.920 --> 15:51.600
ADA: Tommy Shelby? In a library?

15:51.680 --> 15:54.520
TOMMY: I need to borrow a book
about the Russian Revolution.

16:02.960 --> 16:05.160
ADA: Have you got a new wharf
at Maida Vale now?

16:05.640 --> 16:07.480
TOMMY: I've got a new wharf
everywhere now.

16:07.840 --> 16:09.880
ADA: Sometimes, I see our trucks
driving past.

16:10.560 --> 16:11.640
TOMMY: "Our" trucks?

16:12.960 --> 16:14.440
Shelby trucks.

16:15.200 --> 16:16.520
Why the interest?

16:17.120 --> 16:19.360
I just want to broaden my mind.

16:20.000 --> 16:22.680
Well, this is a list of the bastards
who ran away.

16:22.760 --> 16:26.520
And this is written from the point of
view of the peoples' struggle.

16:26.600 --> 16:27.800
Uh-huh.

16:29.840 --> 16:31.520
ADA: There was a Russian
at your wedding.

16:33.320 --> 16:35.480
He wouldn't tell me
how come he got invited.

16:39.000 --> 16:44.040
Well, sometimes,
exiled Russian aristocrats get invited

16:45.360 --> 16:47.440
to social occasions to add
a bit of class.

16:47.720 --> 16:49.120
Is that why he was there?

16:50.480 --> 16:51.800
Why do you want to know?

16:53.040 --> 16:55.760
He was nice.
Maybe I'd like to see him again.

16:55.840 --> 16:57.280
Would that be possible?

16:58.160 --> 16:59.560
No. That would not be possible.

16:59.640 --> 17:01.960
What business do you have
with the Russians, Tommy?

17:04.560 --> 17:05.560
Can I rip this page out?

17:05.640 --> 17:07.120
No, you cannot rip that page out.

17:07.200 --> 17:08.560
-Property of the people.
-(SIGHING)

17:08.800 --> 17:10.280
Tommy, when Arthur
took the Russian away,

17:10.360 --> 17:11.800
he had his killing pistol
under his jacket.

17:11.880 --> 17:14.120
And then Johnny lit a fire in the woods.

17:15.880 --> 17:18.360
You want all the details
because you're bored, Ada.

17:21.120 --> 17:23.720
You used to chase rats
with a revolver, Ada.

17:23.800 --> 17:25.680
-(PEOPLE SHUSHING)
-(SOFTLY) For fuck's sake.

17:25.840 --> 17:28.320
I might just have a job for you
after all.

17:28.440 --> 17:29.520
(SIGHS)

17:37.160 --> 17:39.200
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

17:56.360 --> 17:58.080
Did we run Kempton yesterday or not?

17:58.680 --> 18:00.080
Danny Lee got drunk.

18:00.720 --> 18:02.360
Instead of injecting the horses
with cocaine,

18:02.440 --> 18:03.920
he decided to share it with his cousins.

18:05.120 --> 18:07.040
(SIGHS) Jesus Christ.

18:07.280 --> 18:09.120
He's your brother-in-law.

18:09.240 --> 18:11.080
Tell Esme to speak to him about it.

18:11.600 --> 18:14.520
Look. Before I start...

18:17.480 --> 18:19.480
I don't want you to do anything
about this.

18:20.800 --> 18:21.920
About what?

18:24.160 --> 18:25.320
Vicente Changretta's son.

18:26.280 --> 18:29.360
-The one Lizzie was stepping out with...
-What, Angel?

18:29.480 --> 18:31.520
He's no bigger
than twopence worth of change.

18:31.680 --> 18:34.240
Well, he heard you threatened him
directly to shoot him in the knees.

18:34.320 --> 18:35.520
And now he's going around Nechells

18:35.600 --> 18:37.000
telling everybody
he's going to kill you.

18:38.640 --> 18:41.800
This is Lizzie's fault to start with,
Tommy's for leaving it up to you.

18:41.920 --> 18:43.280
What are you talking about?

18:44.600 --> 18:45.840
We run London.

18:46.240 --> 18:48.200
We run the north,
we run the whole fucking country.

18:48.320 --> 18:50.600
What do we care about
some fucking Nechells Green Eyeties?

18:50.680 --> 18:53.200
We don't need to be getting involved
in all these little piss pots.

18:53.520 --> 18:54.600
What does Arthur say?

18:55.680 --> 18:58.840
That's why I'm here and not him.

18:59.920 --> 19:01.680
If he said it, there'd be a fight.

19:02.520 --> 19:03.520
He says,

19:05.120 --> 19:06.280
"Apologise."

19:08.280 --> 19:09.520
(SNIFFS)

19:10.240 --> 19:11.880
He fucking said what?

19:12.240 --> 19:14.080
POLLY: We own the city.

19:14.520 --> 19:16.720
But we don't need to rub
everybody's noses in it.

19:17.080 --> 19:18.640
If the old man decides to make a stand,

19:18.720 --> 19:20.280
he might get Sabini
feeling sentimental...

19:20.360 --> 19:21.880
JOHN: Sabini's done.

19:25.680 --> 19:27.080
They're all done.

19:28.400 --> 19:30.320
And they all pay up.

19:31.760 --> 19:35.720
But we don't want rebellions.

19:36.000 --> 19:37.120
(SIGHS)

19:38.040 --> 19:40.440
What does, erm, Tommy say?

19:40.720 --> 19:42.920
Tommy's busy. He left me in charge.

19:43.400 --> 19:44.640
And what do you say?

19:49.200 --> 19:51.040
-Compromise.
-Mmm-hmm.

19:52.600 --> 19:54.160
I've asked Lizzie to do it for you.

19:54.600 --> 19:56.960
She's going to meet him,
break up with him for good,

19:57.040 --> 19:59.520
apologise for any inconvenience,
say it was all her fault...

19:59.600 --> 20:01.000
-For fuck's sake!
-(CLATTERING)

20:02.880 --> 20:04.440
You know what all this is?

20:04.640 --> 20:06.320
This is Arthur's fucking missus.

20:06.760 --> 20:08.640
Turn the other fucking cheek?

20:09.200 --> 20:12.440
We'll be handing out Bibles in the
fucking Bull Ring with her cousins.

20:12.520 --> 20:16.280
John, you don't have to do anything.
Lizzie will do it for you.

20:16.360 --> 20:19.840
Then it'll all calm down
and nobody will lose face.

20:19.920 --> 20:21.640
I'll take his fucking face.
How about that?

20:21.720 --> 20:23.440
-(DOOR SLAMS)
-John, do nothing... (SIGHING)

20:32.520 --> 20:35.120
I believe you have a reservation
for a private room

20:35.200 --> 20:36.600
in the name of Mr Romanov.

20:39.240 --> 20:40.480
(CLICKS TONGUE)

20:40.560 --> 20:42.000
You work for Mr Romanov?

20:43.600 --> 20:45.880
-Yes.
-For his household or his office?

20:46.280 --> 20:47.880
(SIGHING) Is there a problem?

20:47.960 --> 20:50.120
I'm afraid without the presence
of the Duke Mikhail Michailovich

20:50.200 --> 20:55.960
or Lady Lewington, we shall have to ask
for payment in advance.

20:56.800 --> 20:57.800
Can I ask why?

20:58.280 --> 21:01.400
Already, Mr Romanov
has four outstanding bills with us.

21:01.880 --> 21:03.920
One for accommodation
and three for dining.

21:04.120 --> 21:07.080
And two banquets, which we wrote off.

21:07.280 --> 21:10.640
We've been asked to be understanding
of our Russian friends by His Majesty.

21:10.720 --> 21:13.000
-But it has been some time now...
-(THUDS)

21:16.640 --> 21:18.600
-May I ask your name, sir?
-Shelby.

21:19.840 --> 21:22.800
Thomas Shelby, and in the future
I will be dining here quite a bit.

21:23.320 --> 21:25.000
Then I shall put you
on our special list.

21:25.080 --> 21:26.120
You do that.

21:27.240 --> 21:28.640
Here is a menu.

21:29.440 --> 21:31.720
I recommend the teal and the pork.

21:32.560 --> 21:35.120
Although your guest, I'm sure,
will order the caviar.

21:35.440 --> 21:38.040
LEON: Myself and my wife and my niece
travel led by train,

21:38.120 --> 21:42.400
then coach, then on foot
through the Villa Ai-Todor in Crimea.

21:42.480 --> 21:45.040
On that journey I lost a toe.

21:45.640 --> 21:49.240
I don't know, I woke up one morning
and it was gone.

21:49.480 --> 21:51.760
All of a sudden I saw a dog,
and it was eating it.

21:52.760 --> 21:54.600
They said the British
had taken pity on us,

21:54.680 --> 21:56.760
and we were taken aboard
<i>HMS Marlborough.</i>

21:57.360 --> 22:00.280
I immediately kissed the steel deck,
my lips froze to it.

22:00.560 --> 22:04.040
And then, of course, I thanked God
and your King for saving us.

22:05.440 --> 22:08.040
Though since then,
he has done nothing but humiliate me.

22:09.720 --> 22:12.080
Who? God or the King?

22:12.200 --> 22:13.640
Sometimes both, Mr Shelby.

22:15.640 --> 22:18.840
Mmm, so, you met my niece already?

22:20.400 --> 22:22.040
Tatiana.

22:22.920 --> 22:25.120
Are you in love with her yet, hmm?

22:26.400 --> 22:29.880
You would be wise
not to love Russian women, you know.

22:30.160 --> 22:31.880
Ah, better not speak of Russian women.

22:31.960 --> 22:34.840
Mmm... That is the worst thing
about being here.

22:35.320 --> 22:37.840
Russian women, they know how to hold it

22:38.360 --> 22:42.160
and most important,
they know exactly when to let it go.

22:43.040 --> 22:44.760
Your cock, I mean.

22:46.280 --> 22:49.000
English women, they do not know so much.
You know?

22:53.560 --> 22:55.840
Did he die well, the spy?

22:58.480 --> 22:59.960
He begged for his life.

23:02.800 --> 23:04.800
I heard you had your brother do it.

23:08.440 --> 23:11.480
So you trust your family, like me.

23:12.960 --> 23:14.800
Like us, Mr Shelby.

23:17.080 --> 23:19.520
Let's talk about trust then, shall we?

23:21.480 --> 23:25.400
You are not a direct relation
to the Romanovs, you are Georgian.

23:25.480 --> 23:26.640
(GLASS SHATTERS)

23:33.240 --> 23:35.600
And the palace where you live
in Hampton Court

23:35.800 --> 23:37.560
is, in fact, a grace and favour house

23:37.640 --> 23:41.120
donated to you, rent-free
by the British Crown.

23:41.320 --> 23:45.240
The maître d' here, tells me
that you are in some debt.

23:45.960 --> 23:48.280
Both here and other places, I imagine.

23:49.080 --> 23:53.360
See, I've been given 10,
but I've been promised 40.

23:55.520 --> 23:57.200
Already, I have had to
have a man killed.

23:58.000 --> 24:00.120
That sort of work does not come cheap.

24:01.600 --> 24:02.960
Do you understand?

24:28.880 --> 24:30.960
Let me tell you something, Mr Shelby.

24:33.400 --> 24:34.960
Before we boarded the ship,

24:35.040 --> 24:38.800
my niece sewed 16 diamonds
into her velvet dress,

24:38.880 --> 24:43.040
and also she had two sapphires
in her intimate places.

24:44.360 --> 24:48.480
My wife managed two sapphires
and five diamonds.

24:49.440 --> 24:52.920
This is already
for the killing of the spy

24:53.480 --> 24:56.200
and a down payment on future services.

24:59.520 --> 25:01.880
Now, tell me,
where do you keep these things?

25:02.000 --> 25:03.280
In a bank?

25:04.080 --> 25:06.560
How could we plead poverty
around London society

25:06.640 --> 25:09.040
if we used banks, Mr Shelby?

25:10.920 --> 25:12.800
Well, you should know...

25:13.840 --> 25:16.520
Hatton Gardens is not safe.

25:17.800 --> 25:19.840
That's why we have our own treasury.

25:23.200 --> 25:26.960
Very well, I shall have
my people check its veracity.

25:28.840 --> 25:30.000
(TOMMY GRUNTS SOFTLY)

25:32.400 --> 25:36.680
Before the revolution began,
we were soft and weak.

25:37.480 --> 25:38.800
We made compromise.

25:39.720 --> 25:41.240
But let me tell you.

25:42.320 --> 25:45.240
We will never be soft and weak again.

25:46.000 --> 25:47.560
Do you understand?

25:51.040 --> 25:52.320
Good day, Mr Shelby.

26:13.400 --> 26:15.360
MAN: This way, Mr Changretta.

26:15.800 --> 26:17.560
(MAN SPEAKING CANTONESE)

26:18.400 --> 26:20.280
Just there, sir. There.

26:22.640 --> 26:24.240
(YELLING IN CANTONESE)

26:48.280 --> 26:49.600
(SQUELCHING)

26:56.520 --> 26:58.000
ANGEL: Are you going to kill me?

26:58.600 --> 27:00.480
JOHN: Get fucking up.

27:00.560 --> 27:02.000
Stay away from Lizzie!

27:02.520 --> 27:04.200
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

27:07.600 --> 27:09.400
-(SLICING)
-(ANGEL GROANING)

27:10.880 --> 27:12.320
(SCREAMING)

27:13.080 --> 27:17.120
By order of the Peaky fucking Blinders!

27:17.200 --> 27:18.440
(ANGEL CONTINUES SCREAMING)

27:32.720 --> 27:34.320
TOMMY: Going to introduce me, Michael?

27:35.000 --> 27:38.240
This is Charlotte Murray.
Her father makes cars.

27:40.760 --> 27:42.960
I really enjoyed your wedding,
Mr Shelby.

27:44.960 --> 27:47.920
Polly said that you should call her.
There's been some trouble.

27:48.040 --> 27:49.320
TOMMY: What trouble?

27:51.040 --> 27:53.800
I'm guessing it's stuff
she doesn't like to tell me about.

27:56.000 --> 27:57.200
TOMMY: Nice to meet you.

28:03.320 --> 28:04.640
(CHUCKLING)

28:13.440 --> 28:15.800
ARTHUR: All right, Finn.
Thanks for coming. Fuck off.

28:17.440 --> 28:19.400
Finn, you can stay.

28:22.520 --> 28:24.480
(INHALES SHARPLY) Sit down, John.

28:24.560 --> 28:25.760
Sit down.

28:32.000 --> 28:33.920
John, you cut Angel Changretta.

28:35.920 --> 28:38.080
Even though Arthur told you
to apologise.

28:38.160 --> 28:39.200
JOHN: Mmm-hmm.

28:39.480 --> 28:41.720
TOMMY: Polly told you to compromise.
JOHN: Mmm-hmm.

28:42.200 --> 28:45.520
You chose not to listen to Mr Apologise
or Mrs Compromise.

28:47.320 --> 28:50.000
And now I have got an Italian
walking around my backyard

28:50.120 --> 28:52.080
saying he's going to kill my brother.

28:53.880 --> 28:57.040
So what do we do, John.
Do we apologise or do we compromise?

29:04.320 --> 29:06.960
Oh, it was just something
John said as a joke.

29:08.520 --> 29:10.240
Yeah, but he's your brother
as well, Arthur.

29:10.800 --> 29:12.000
Yeah.

29:12.680 --> 29:14.200
I know I didn't want to start a war

29:14.280 --> 29:16.400
over something John said
without meaning it.

29:20.440 --> 29:24.000
So, should he apologise in Italian
or in English?

29:27.560 --> 29:30.480
Or should we ask them
which fucking language they prefer?

29:30.840 --> 29:31.960
I'm not clear.

29:35.240 --> 29:37.120
You said while this business
was going on in London,

29:37.200 --> 29:38.280
you wanted peace at home.

29:38.360 --> 29:39.920
And the only way to guarantee peace

29:40.000 --> 29:42.920
is by making the prospect of war
seem hopeless.

29:43.480 --> 29:47.640
If you apologise once,
you do it again and again and again.

29:47.760 --> 29:50.160
Like taking bricks out of the wall
of your fucking house.

29:50.360 --> 29:51.840
Do you want
to bring the house down, Arthur?

29:51.920 --> 29:52.920
(ARTHUR GRUNTS)

29:53.000 --> 29:54.960
If you're soft on rebellion, it'll grow.

29:55.040 --> 29:56.960
Bloody "soft on rebellion".

29:57.040 --> 29:58.920
You did the right thing, John.

29:59.000 --> 30:00.280
Now, we go on the offensive.

30:00.360 --> 30:03.640
We take two of the Changretta pubs,
and we take them tonight. That's it.

30:03.720 --> 30:06.000
Oh! Right. For Christ's sake, why?

30:06.080 --> 30:07.240
-Hey.
-Why?

30:07.320 --> 30:09.160
TOMMY: Why? Because we fucking can.

30:09.440 --> 30:12.600
Because we fucking can
and if we can, we do.

30:12.920 --> 30:16.760
And if we lift our heel off their necks
now, they'll just come at us.

30:18.880 --> 30:22.720
Remember these are the bastards
that wanted Danny Whizz-Bang dead.

30:28.240 --> 30:29.720
You're getting soft, brother.

30:29.840 --> 30:31.200
Soft and weak.

30:31.840 --> 30:33.960
Save the Bible for Sundays, eh.

30:38.200 --> 30:39.320
Finn?

30:39.920 --> 30:42.320
I need to get to Hockley and then home.

30:42.400 --> 30:44.200
It's been a long day.

30:48.280 --> 30:51.640
You take the Wrexham,
you take the Five Bells.

30:51.720 --> 30:54.480
You get them signed over to us
in the morning.

30:54.560 --> 30:56.200
You make sure the coppers stay away.

30:58.800 --> 31:02.680
Don't use the fucking phones, all right?
There's someone listening.

31:11.320 --> 31:12.640
ARTHUR: Well done.

31:19.280 --> 31:20.920
(POLLY SLURPING)

31:36.000 --> 31:37.680
(RINGING)

31:45.960 --> 31:47.080
(SPEAKS RUSSIAN)

32:41.040 --> 32:42.400
Hmm.

33:02.400 --> 33:03.800
(WIND HOWLING)

33:06.600 --> 33:09.160
(MUSIC PLAYING
OVER GRAMOPHONE)

33:09.240 --> 33:10.920
Not hungry, Mrs Shelby?

33:11.040 --> 33:14.280
"Hungry"? Oh, no. Sorry, Mary.

33:15.160 --> 33:16.560
You'll ruin your eyes.

33:20.560 --> 33:21.560
Tommy...

33:30.720 --> 33:32.480
-TOMMY: Hello.
-Hello.

33:34.760 --> 33:36.640
-Sit down.
-(CLEARS THROAT)

33:41.240 --> 33:43.280
-Guess.
-Guess what?

33:48.480 --> 33:50.200
-He said yes.
-Who?

33:51.000 --> 33:54.880
The leader of the Birmingham City
Council is going to attend the dinner.

33:56.840 --> 34:00.040
-Everyone has said yes. Everyone.
-Ah. (CLEARS THROAT)

34:00.120 --> 34:02.320
I keep having to change the catering.

34:03.560 --> 34:05.840
And my writing hand is almost
falling off.

34:06.080 --> 34:07.960
Oh, what are you writing for?
I bought you a typewriter.

34:08.240 --> 34:11.840
(CHUCKLES) You don't write letters
of a social occasion on a typewriter.

34:11.920 --> 34:14.360
-Oh. Forgive me.
-(CHUCKLES)

34:16.440 --> 34:19.240
I have the drawings

34:19.320 --> 34:22.120
of what they plan to do
with the grounds of the house.

34:22.200 --> 34:24.800
There'll be an area
for the children to play. Look.

34:24.880 --> 34:26.000
Mmm-hmm.

34:26.080 --> 34:28.440
And the Birmingham Charity Commission
have agreed to set aside

34:28.520 --> 34:33.040
their three rotten floorboards upstairs
and grant us the licence within a month.

34:36.480 --> 34:39.840
-You're not listening to me.
-Yes I am. I am.

34:40.240 --> 34:42.720
Do you think I'm becoming obsessed?

34:43.800 --> 34:44.800
Yes.

34:46.280 --> 34:48.640
Should I ask you how your day was,
like a good wife?

34:49.280 --> 34:50.280
No.

34:53.240 --> 34:56.440
I'm guessing that means your day
was not as successful as mine, hmm.

34:56.960 --> 34:59.840
That all depends
on how you measure success.

35:01.160 --> 35:03.320
See, personally,

35:04.680 --> 35:06.040
I measure it in sapphires.

35:06.440 --> 35:07.800
(CHUCKLING) Oh!

35:08.480 --> 35:10.800
-Sapphires. Mmm.
-Uh-huh.

35:13.120 --> 35:14.720
Close your eyes.

35:15.520 --> 35:16.840
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

35:17.760 --> 35:19.360
(WHISPERS) Close your eyes.

35:35.840 --> 35:37.920
All right, you can open 'em.

35:39.880 --> 35:42.120
Where the hell did you get that?

35:43.720 --> 35:44.880
It's beautiful.

35:48.280 --> 35:50.360
You can wear it to the
foundation dinner.

35:52.320 --> 35:54.920
Don't you think it's a bit much
for a charity dinner?

35:55.200 --> 35:56.400
Grace,

35:57.200 --> 35:59.000
this is fucking Birmingham.

36:00.080 --> 36:03.400
"Good taste" is for people
who can't afford sapphires.

36:03.480 --> 36:05.040
(CHUCKLING)

36:05.120 --> 36:06.720
Oh, Mr Shelby.

36:09.040 --> 36:10.840
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

36:35.480 --> 36:37.760
Did you wind the clock, Arthur?

36:40.800 --> 36:42.560
We should go to bed.

36:44.200 --> 36:45.880
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

36:48.240 --> 36:49.640
I need to...

36:50.720 --> 36:52.360
I need to go out.

36:54.000 --> 36:56.080
Some business I need to do.

37:02.560 --> 37:03.880
"Business"?

37:10.040 --> 37:11.720
But you only just got in.

37:11.920 --> 37:12.920
I won't be long.

37:13.000 --> 37:14.360
LINDA: It's 10 o'clock.

37:16.160 --> 37:17.480
It's pouring with rain.

37:19.200 --> 37:20.320
I'll go...

37:21.280 --> 37:22.960
I'll go and I'll come back.

37:23.760 --> 37:24.760
Arthur.

37:28.440 --> 37:31.160
Working in the dark is for the devil.

37:32.040 --> 37:33.520
We said.

37:34.320 --> 37:36.480
Start to do your work in the light.

37:38.080 --> 37:39.600
Your own light.

37:40.760 --> 37:42.400
Inside your head.

37:44.840 --> 37:46.600
It's just paperwork.

37:57.400 --> 38:00.920
I need you to clear your men
out of Nechells tonight.

38:04.520 --> 38:09.520
I thought you boys were a bit grand
for this sort of thing these days.

38:09.600 --> 38:10.680
Moss.

38:11.920 --> 38:15.320
Mind you,
I think Tommy enjoys the sport.

38:18.880 --> 38:20.200
Something like that.

38:21.480 --> 38:22.960
Good night, Arthur.

38:23.040 --> 38:24.200
Night.

38:38.280 --> 38:40.240
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

39:03.200 --> 39:04.560
JOHN: Arthur, what are you doing?

39:09.920 --> 39:11.160
Arthur?

39:14.200 --> 39:16.320
We're going to the Garrison.

39:16.400 --> 39:19.000
ARTHUR: No. I'm going home, John.

39:21.800 --> 39:23.720
JOHN: Go and fuck yourself, Arthur.

39:24.920 --> 39:26.440
Yeah! Fuck off!

39:31.200 --> 39:33.040
(ANGEL SCREAMING)

39:38.400 --> 39:39.560
(NURSE SHUSHING)

39:43.320 --> 39:45.320
(SPEAKS ITALIAN)

40:15.200 --> 40:16.880
TOMMY: Come here, Charlie.
GRACE: Charlie.

40:19.120 --> 40:22.240
This big man and his brother
are going to make us a lot of money.

40:22.640 --> 40:23.880
Or lose us a lot of money.

40:24.000 --> 40:27.480
Who the hell cares
when they are such beautiful beasts, eh?

40:29.200 --> 40:31.640
(CHARLIE BABBLING)

40:35.640 --> 40:37.440
(INDISTINCT)

40:41.520 --> 40:42.680
Go on.

40:55.120 --> 40:56.680
(ESME MOANING)

41:00.560 --> 41:03.040
TOMMY: You've got a house, John.
JOHN: Oh, fuck.

41:05.320 --> 41:06.320
Full of kids.

41:06.400 --> 41:08.040
TOMMY: Well, you've got a maid
to look after the kids.

41:08.120 --> 41:09.520
JOHN: Yeah, she listens.

41:12.840 --> 41:14.880
TOMMY: Have you done the odds
for tomorrow?

41:14.960 --> 41:17.080
Something urgent came up.

41:17.160 --> 41:19.480
JOHN: They get worse
when they're pregnant, Tom.

41:20.480 --> 41:21.480
John.

41:21.840 --> 41:24.920
Esme, I need you to leave now.
Go out the back door,

41:25.040 --> 41:26.280
and lock it after you.

41:28.800 --> 41:30.400
Come on, I left the office.

41:31.080 --> 41:33.840
There's two trucks full of coppers
out there, John.

41:34.760 --> 41:35.840
Where the fuck is Arthur?

41:36.000 --> 41:38.640
He goes home to the Madonna of Moseley
on the stroke of five.

41:38.720 --> 41:41.520
-ESME: You need to talk to him, Tom.
-Esme, please, go. Now.

41:41.760 --> 41:42.760
Please.

41:43.320 --> 41:44.720
This is very fucking unusual.

41:44.880 --> 41:46.000
So, call Moss.

41:46.120 --> 41:49.600
They're from out of town.
London, by the looks of their boots.

41:49.680 --> 41:51.080
Since when are we
scared of coppers, Tom?

41:51.160 --> 41:52.280
(GUN CLICKING)

41:52.360 --> 41:53.600
-Since things changed, John.
-(ESME SCREAMING)

41:55.200 --> 41:57.000
OFFICER 1 : Scotland Yard!
OFFICER 2: Get down! Police!

41:57.080 --> 41:58.680
OFFICER 1 : Go on!
TOMMY: John!

41:59.160 --> 42:00.960
(CLAMOURING)

42:01.040 --> 42:03.000
John! John, it's the Yard.

42:03.360 --> 42:04.400
Put it down.

42:04.480 --> 42:05.600
Putting it down.
Putting it fucking down.

42:05.680 --> 42:08.120
-Hands on your heads!
-Down on your knees! Now!

42:08.760 --> 42:11.040
Let her fucking go!
She's fucking pregnant.

42:12.000 --> 42:13.160
Leave her alone.

42:13.240 --> 42:14.680
What the fuck is happening, Tom?

42:14.760 --> 42:16.880
-OFFICER 1 : Let's go.
-(ESME SCREAMS)

42:17.280 --> 42:18.560
ESME: Put me down!

42:18.640 --> 42:21.880
-Tell Polly it's Russian business, John.
-All right.

42:21.960 --> 42:24.640
Peaky fucking Blinders my arse.

42:27.760 --> 42:30.360
-HUGHES: Is he afraid?
-No.

42:35.040 --> 42:36.600
Go on.

42:41.360 --> 42:42.440
Sit.

42:45.920 --> 42:48.160
I'm talking to you, Mr Shelby.

42:50.360 --> 42:51.480
(SCOFFS)

43:00.600 --> 43:03.480
So, the Odd Fellows want you to know
that any deviation

43:03.560 --> 43:06.440
from your instructions
will have consequences.

43:07.000 --> 43:08.160
What's your dog's name?

43:10.480 --> 43:11.840
You visited your sister.

43:12.320 --> 43:14.240
Eh? What's your name, boy?

43:14.360 --> 43:15.880
(SNARLING)

43:16.640 --> 43:19.360
Your sister is a potential
security breach.

43:20.280 --> 43:23.080
She has connections
with the Bolsheviks in London

43:23.560 --> 43:25.560
who have connections
with the Soviet Embassy.

43:25.680 --> 43:27.600
I think
I will just call your dog, "Boy".

43:29.520 --> 43:31.840
You love your Boy, don't you?

43:34.440 --> 43:35.880
Understand this.

43:37.200 --> 43:40.000
You have the local police
in your pocket,

43:40.320 --> 43:42.160
we have Scotland Yard.

43:43.560 --> 43:46.640
They do what we tell them
just as surely as this dog.

43:47.680 --> 43:48.800
Let him off the leash.

43:51.280 --> 43:53.200
Are you hearing me, Mr Shelby?

43:53.800 --> 43:55.760
I can charm dogs.

43:56.800 --> 43:58.440
Gypsy witchcraft.

43:59.480 --> 44:02.920
And those I can't charm,
I can kill with my own hands.

44:05.400 --> 44:07.560
You learn it
when you have a dog on a boat.

44:07.640 --> 44:09.920
They go fucking mad in tunnels.

44:11.240 --> 44:13.440
I feel like I'm in a tunnel now.

44:15.040 --> 44:18.720
You know that feeling,
when you have to kill or be killed?

44:23.800 --> 44:25.480
Let the dog off the leash

44:26.120 --> 44:28.360
and give the order you give in Gaelic...

44:29.960 --> 44:31.120
Like I'm told you do

44:31.200 --> 44:34.800
when someone displeases you
or someone reports you.

44:35.880 --> 44:39.320
Visit your sister again
and she will die crossing the road.

44:42.640 --> 44:44.680
(SPEAKS IN ROMANY)

44:47.080 --> 44:48.520
(IN ENGLISH) Then you say it.

44:54.680 --> 44:57.520
If you wanted me dead,
I would be dead, wouldn't I?

44:57.680 --> 44:59.040
(SCOFFS)

45:00.560 --> 45:01.920
It's true.

45:03.000 --> 45:04.880
It's true, we do need you alive.

45:06.400 --> 45:08.400
But when you go home today,
Mr Shelby...

45:09.960 --> 45:12.560
Be sure to check
under your little boy's pillow.

45:13.600 --> 45:15.600
The tooth fairy has been.

45:18.440 --> 45:20.200
We can reach anyone.

45:20.720 --> 45:21.960
Anywhere.

45:24.040 --> 45:25.320
(KNOCKING)

45:51.920 --> 45:53.320
(CHARLIE CRYING)

46:02.400 --> 46:04.720
-Is everything all right?
-(PANTING) Yes.

46:05.200 --> 46:06.920
Everything's fine. Everything's fine.

46:07.560 --> 46:08.560
Yeah.

46:08.920 --> 46:11.120
You promised, Tommy.

46:11.200 --> 46:12.760
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

46:12.840 --> 46:14.640
I trust you.

46:17.520 --> 46:19.200
-I trust you, Tommy.
-Yes.

46:22.000 --> 46:24.800
(SOFTLY) He's fine. He's fine.

46:26.000 --> 46:27.760
(CHARLIE CRYING)

46:35.120 --> 46:37.160
Grace. Grace.

46:38.240 --> 46:39.800
(WHISPERING) Come on.

46:53.680 --> 46:55.480
You're not one of those
impressionists, are you?

46:55.600 --> 46:57.280
They're all terribly political,
aren't they?

46:58.440 --> 47:00.200
-And you're not?
-Goodness no.

47:00.840 --> 47:03.960
The people I work for just
want me to paint what is there.

47:04.040 --> 47:06.680
To me, politics is deliberately
making things better

47:06.760 --> 47:09.480
for some people by deliberately
making them worse for others.

47:09.560 --> 47:10.680
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

47:16.960 --> 47:18.520
Well, I thought I might wear this.

47:22.560 --> 47:24.600
Oh, God. It's too much.
I'll try something more simple.

47:24.720 --> 47:26.400
No. Don't...

47:28.480 --> 47:30.680
Suddenly, I feel incompetent.

47:31.400 --> 47:34.400
I want the portrait to hang in the
office, so I want it to look formal.

47:34.480 --> 47:36.080
RUBEN: It's not formal.

47:36.920 --> 47:38.440
It's beautiful.

47:40.400 --> 47:41.600
It was made in Paris.

47:42.240 --> 47:43.840
It was stolen in Birmingham.
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

47:44.160 --> 47:47.640
My mother stole it from a house
she was cleaning. 1901.

47:47.720 --> 47:49.120
RUBEN: No. No.

47:49.200 --> 47:50.960
It's yours. It belongs on you.

47:52.240 --> 47:54.440
A woman of substance and class.

47:54.520 --> 47:56.560
Believe me. I've painted many women

47:56.640 --> 47:58.720
who don't belong
in their expensive dresses.

48:00.960 --> 48:02.200
There'll be no charge.

48:02.880 --> 48:04.520
Your normal rate.

48:04.960 --> 48:07.120
-I insist.
-Hmm! There's a first.

48:09.520 --> 48:12.120
-So, when shall we start?
-I've already started.

48:13.200 --> 48:14.960
Come to my studio this evening.

48:15.080 --> 48:17.600
-POLLY: Uh, I am busy this evening.
-Polly, invite him.

48:18.640 --> 48:19.640
Invite me to what?

48:19.720 --> 48:21.720
Ada, this is a professional transaction.

48:21.800 --> 48:24.240
-Invite me to what?
-ADA: Shelby Foundation dinner.

48:24.320 --> 48:26.600
-Polly's going alone. You're invited...
-POLLY: Ada.

48:30.000 --> 48:32.480
I'll come to your studio on Sunday.

48:33.480 --> 48:35.440
And then we shall begin.

49:26.320 --> 49:28.520
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

49:37.360 --> 49:39.120
A woman of substance...

49:41.160 --> 49:42.480
...and class.

49:50.720 --> 49:52.800
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

50:00.120 --> 50:01.120
Hello.

50:02.840 --> 50:03.840
WOMAN: Hello, Polly.

50:12.080 --> 50:14.480
(INDISTINCT)

50:20.120 --> 50:21.320
Tommy.

50:23.360 --> 50:25.560
Here's the leader
of the Birmingham City Council.

50:25.760 --> 50:27.120
-Hello, Tommy.
-Hi, Danny.

50:27.200 --> 50:28.480
DANIEL: How's business?

50:28.560 --> 50:30.680
TOMMY: All right, it's holding up,
holding up. How are you?

50:31.200 --> 50:32.320
You know each other?

50:33.040 --> 50:36.160
DANIEL: (CHUCKLES) I have interests
in a steelworks in Cradley Heath.

50:36.240 --> 50:39.720
Tommy helps me get my products
to the carmakers.

50:39.920 --> 50:42.640
Congratulations, Mrs Shelby,
on your wedding.

50:42.720 --> 50:44.960
Thank you,
I'm surprised you weren't invited.

50:45.040 --> 50:46.920
Now, how would that look, eh?

50:48.600 --> 50:51.480
Oh, now, the party has really started.

50:51.560 --> 50:52.720
Who are they?

50:52.880 --> 50:56.600
DANIEL: Father John Hughes
from St Mary's Boys Reformatory.

50:56.680 --> 50:59.880
And with him is Mr Patrick Jarvis, MP.

50:59.960 --> 51:04.800
They are part of an organisation
called the Economic League.

51:04.880 --> 51:06.600
Did you invite them, Grace?

51:06.800 --> 51:08.280
Their names sound familiar.

51:09.160 --> 51:11.000
They were recommended by the Lord Mayor.

51:11.080 --> 51:14.280
Oh. On your
"best people of the city" list, eh?

51:14.480 --> 51:16.840
-GRACE: Do you know them?
-I'll introduce you, Tommy.

51:16.920 --> 51:20.320
That's all right, Danny.
I'll introduce myself.

51:34.560 --> 51:37.000
We appear to have taken you by surprise.

51:37.520 --> 51:39.160
I have adjusted.

51:40.760 --> 51:43.040
Since the socialists
got into Downing Street

51:43.120 --> 51:44.320
we are all being followed.

51:44.400 --> 51:46.680
We have to meet in places
where we'd meet anyway.

51:46.760 --> 51:48.080
You should have stopped by Small Heath.

51:48.160 --> 51:50.040
I could have given you
a more traditional welcome.

51:50.120 --> 51:53.640
-They want to know about ammunition.
-PATRICK: And chains for the wheels.

51:53.720 --> 51:56.200
When the White Guard
make their run for Tbilisi,

51:56.280 --> 51:57.880
it will be over rough terrain.

51:58.120 --> 52:01.640
(INHALES SHARPLY) The chains are
suitable for snow or wet ground.

52:01.720 --> 52:03.520
They're already stored on the vehicles.

52:03.600 --> 52:05.480
There's a batch of weapons
set aside at the BSA,

52:05.560 --> 52:07.320
which is bound for the Turkish army.

52:07.640 --> 52:09.920
And how will you get it all aboard
the London train?

52:10.000 --> 52:12.240
There will be a strike that night
across the city.

52:13.000 --> 52:15.560
You will have to stop
the train twice. How?

52:16.360 --> 52:19.240
Two drivers will join the strike
at different points.

52:20.960 --> 52:26.240
Rather fun, getting the Communist unions
to help get weapons to the Whites.

52:26.320 --> 52:27.840
TOMMY: Yes, rather fun, eh?

52:29.200 --> 52:31.360
I am thinking ahead,
thinking of every possibility,

52:31.440 --> 52:33.240
remembering everything
that is happening.

52:33.360 --> 52:34.680
(PATRICK SCOFFS)

52:36.240 --> 52:38.560
The Russians want to inspect
the vehicles.

52:40.040 --> 52:42.360
-I'll take photographs.
-PATRICK: Mmm-mmm.

52:42.440 --> 52:45.480
The Duke has sent his niece, she's here.

52:46.400 --> 52:49.120
Tomorrow you will take her to the
factory and show her.

52:49.200 --> 52:52.880
No. Union conveners
are watching the factories.

52:54.760 --> 52:55.800
Not possible.

52:57.080 --> 53:00.200
Anything is possible, Mr Shelby.

53:00.280 --> 53:01.960
You will take her.

53:02.920 --> 53:05.320
You will pick her up
from this hotel at ten.

53:06.840 --> 53:09.640
Now, look, a priest with an empty glass.

53:11.000 --> 53:13.160
Let's get back to the party.

53:15.120 --> 53:20.160
You know, gentlemen, there is hell
and there is another place below hell.

53:21.960 --> 53:24.000
I will remember everything...

53:24.920 --> 53:26.640
And forget nothing.

53:31.320 --> 53:33.280
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

53:36.320 --> 53:37.600
GRACE: Tommy,

53:37.680 --> 53:39.880
this is Duchess Tatiana Petrovna.

53:40.040 --> 53:41.360
(CLEARS THROAT)

53:41.440 --> 53:43.600
Come on, Tommy, aren't you impressed
to meet a real duchess?

53:43.800 --> 53:45.720
Well, I understand they charge a fee.

53:45.960 --> 53:48.720
(SCOFFS) Mr Shelby,
you are very direct.

53:48.800 --> 53:50.080
Too direct.

53:50.160 --> 53:51.360
TATIANA: (CHUCKLES) But it's true.

53:52.000 --> 53:54.320
I attend these things for the champagne.

53:54.480 --> 53:56.880
And for the chance
to be treated like a duchess again.

53:57.240 --> 53:59.920
You should have kissed my hand,
Mr Shelby.

54:02.160 --> 54:03.520
Forgive me.

54:05.960 --> 54:07.720
She was asking about my sapphire.

54:07.800 --> 54:10.800
-I thought I recognised it.
-She said it was Russian.

54:10.880 --> 54:13.760
My husband has business in Russia.
Perhaps you know about it, Tatiana?

54:13.840 --> 54:15.640
Well, tonight is not a night
for business, eh?

54:15.720 --> 54:17.680
Is that why you were in the concert hall
for 10 minutes?

54:17.760 --> 54:19.040
I think people are ready
for dinner now, Grace.

54:19.240 --> 54:21.320
No, no. I'm not done
pumping people for money.

54:21.520 --> 54:22.920
What is "pump for money"?

54:23.080 --> 54:25.040
It's what I do every day.

54:25.720 --> 54:27.400
You know each other, do you?

54:28.360 --> 54:30.400
You see, I am in charge
of compiling the list of guests,

54:30.480 --> 54:32.760
but it's my husband
who seems to know all of them.

54:32.840 --> 54:34.360
I hear he is very well connected.

54:34.440 --> 54:36.320
And where does a duchess hear that?

54:36.480 --> 54:37.520
In certain circles.

54:37.600 --> 54:38.840
All right, enough. Ada.

54:38.960 --> 54:40.520
Grace, there's a Lady Dowager

54:40.600 --> 54:42.640
who wants to speak to you
about coffee mornings.

54:42.720 --> 54:44.960
She mentioned a £2,000 cash donation.

54:45.120 --> 54:47.240
Tatiana, you and I will speak later.

54:47.320 --> 54:48.840
TATIANA: I would like that.

54:51.080 --> 54:53.240
Going to the factory tomorrow
is a mistake.

54:54.280 --> 54:55.960
Nevertheless, we will go.

54:57.360 --> 55:00.680
Also, my uncle ordered me to seduce you
to give us an advantage.

55:00.760 --> 55:03.280
But with a beautiful wife like that
it will be difficult, no?

55:03.360 --> 55:04.840
Tomorrow is a mistake.

55:05.200 --> 55:07.680
Have you not heard?
We have no morals, we Russians.

55:07.880 --> 55:08.960
And no fucking sense.

55:09.040 --> 55:10.560
And no options.

55:11.040 --> 55:14.280
I would fuck you for the cause.
What do you think of that?

55:15.320 --> 55:17.520
I think you should not drink
vodka with champagne.

55:18.960 --> 55:21.320
TATIANA: Does your wife know
that the sapphire she is wearing

55:21.400 --> 55:23.440
has been cursed by a Gypsy?

55:24.440 --> 55:26.000
(CHUCKLING)

55:27.640 --> 55:28.640
What did you say?

55:29.040 --> 55:32.160
Nothing on Earth would make me wear it.

55:47.000 --> 55:49.160
Grace, listen to me.
Look, I can explain.

55:49.360 --> 55:50.360
-Go away.
-It's...

55:50.440 --> 55:51.640
MC: Ladies and gentlemen.

55:51.720 --> 55:52.880
For once, you shouldn't have to explain.

55:52.960 --> 55:56.320
The loyalty toast,
to His Majesty the King.

55:56.440 --> 55:58.200
ALL: To the King.

55:58.600 --> 56:00.120
MC: Dinner is served.

56:00.320 --> 56:02.360
TOMMY: You look beautiful,
but you need to take this off.

56:02.440 --> 56:04.000
Why? Because you think
it would look better on her?

56:04.080 --> 56:06.800
Grace, look at me,
fuck these people, eh.

56:06.880 --> 56:09.960
Fuck 'em, I need you to be all right.

56:10.280 --> 56:13.760
I need you, Grace. I need you.

56:21.080 --> 56:23.320
Damn you, Tommy Shelby. (CHUCKLES)

56:34.680 --> 56:36.160
(CHUCKLES)

56:36.240 --> 56:37.760
-Shall we go inside?
-Yeah.

56:40.880 --> 56:42.320
For Angel!

56:43.840 --> 56:45.000
(GUNSHOT)

56:45.200 --> 56:47.120
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

56:55.640 --> 56:58.880
Get me a fucking ambulance now!

57:41.640 --> 57:43.640
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

57:43.664 --> 57:48.664
http://hiqve.com/
